6.3 PERCENT IN ASIA PACIFIC, 4.9 PERCENT IN THE UNITED STATES, 4.5 PERCENT IN LATIN AMERICA/CANADA, AND 3.2 PERCENT IN EMEA. FOR THE COMPANY IN TOTAL, ORGANIC LOCAL-CURRENCY SALES GREW 4.9 PERCENT, WITH HIGHER ORGANIC VOLUMES CONTRIBUTING 3.9 PERCENT AND SELLING PRICE INCREASES CONTRIBUTING 1.0 PERCENT. ACQUISITIONS ADDED 0.1 PERCENT TO SALES, DRIVEN BY THE TREO ACQUISITION. FOREIGN CURRENCY TRANSLATION REDUCED SALES BY 1.9 PERCENT YEAR-ON-YEAR.

