RETURN ON INVESTED CAPITAL (NON-GAAP MEASURE).

THE COMPANY USES NON-GAAP MEASURES TO FOCUS ON SHAREHOLDER VALUE CREATION. 3M USES RETURN ON INVESTED CAPITAL (ROIC), DEFINED AS ANNUALIZED AFTER-TAX OPERATING INCOME (INCLUDING INTEREST INCOME) DIVIDED BY AVERAGE OPERATING CAPITAL. OPERATING CAPITAL IS DEFINED AS NET ASSETS (TOTAL ASSETS LESS TOTAL LIABILITIES) EXCLUDING DEBT. THIS MEASURE IS NOT RECOGNIZED UNDER U.S. GAAP AND MAY NOT BE COMPARABLE TO SIMILARLY TITLED MEASURES USED BY OTHER COMPANIES. ROIC WAS

