FREE CASH FLOW (NON-GAAP MEASURE).

IN ADDITION, TO NET CASH PROVIDED BY OPERATING ACTIVITIES, 3M BELIEVES FREE CASH FLOW AND FREE CASH FLOW CONVERSION ARE USEFUL MEASURES OF PERFORMANCE AND USES THESE MEASURES AS AN INDICATION OF THE STRENGTH OF THE COMPANY AND ITS ABILITY TO GENERATE CASH. FREE CASH FLOW AND FREE CASH FLOW CONVERSION ARE NOT DEFINED UNDER U.S. GENERALLY ACCEPTED ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES (GAAP). THEREFORE, THEY SHOULD NOT BE CONSIDERED A SUBSTITUTE FOR INCOME OR CASH FLOW DATA PREPARED IN ACCORDANCE WITH U.S. GAAP AND MAY NOT BE COMPARABLE TO SIMILARLY TITLED MEASURES USED BY OTHER COMPANIES. 3M DEFINES FREE CASH FLOW AS NET CASH PROVIDED BY OPERATING ACTIVITIES LESS PURCHASES OF PROPERTY, PLANT AND EQUIPMENT (WHICH IS CLASSIFIED AS AN INVESTING ACTIVITY). IT SHOULD NOT BE INFERRED THAT THE ENTIRE FREE CASH FLOW AMOUNT IS AVAILABLE FOR DISCRETIONARY EXPENDITURES. 3M DEFINES FREE CASH FLOW CONVERSION AS FREE CASH FLOW DIVIDED BY NET INCOME ATTRIBUTABLE TO 3M. BELOW FIND A RECAP OF FREE CASH FLOW AND FREE CASH FLOW CONVERSION FOR

2015

