PERCENTAGE POINTS, IMPACTED BY SEVERAL FACTORS. FACTORS WHICH INCREASED THE COMPANY’S EFFECTIVE TAX RATE INCLUDED INTERNATIONAL TAXES, WHICH WERE IMPACTED BY CHANGES IN FOREIGN CURRENCY RATES AND CHANGES TO THE GEOGRAPHIC MIX OF INCOME BEFORE TAXES, AND OTHER ITEMS. COMBINED, THESE FACTORS INCREASED THE COMPANY’S EFFECTIVE TAX RATE BY

2.4

PERCENTAGE POINTS. THIS INCREASE WAS PARTIALLY OFFSET BY A

2.2

PERCENTAGE POINT DECREASE, WHICH RELATED TO THE REMEASUREMENTS OF 3M’S UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS, INCLUDING THE RESTORATION OF TAX BASIS ON CERTAIN ASSETS FOR WHICH DEPRECIATION DEDUCTIONS WERE PREVIOUSLY LIMITED, AND INCREASES IN THE DOMESTIC MANUFACTURER’S DEDUCTION AND U.S. RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT CREDIT BENEFITS.

