NOTE 16

. BUSINESS SEGMENTS

3M’S BUSINESSES ARE ORGANIZED, MANAGED AND INTERNALLY GROUPED INTO SEGMENTS BASED ON DIFFERENCES IN MARKETS, PRODUCTS, TECHNOLOGIES AND SERVICES. 3M MANAGES ITS OPERATIONS IN

FIVE

BUSINESS SEGMENTS: INDUSTRIAL; SAFETY AND GRAPHICS; HEALTH CARE;

ELECTRONICS AND ENERGY;

AND CONSUMER. 3M’S FIVE BUSINESS SEGMENTS BRING TOGETHER COMMON OR RELATED 3M TECHNOLOGIES, ENHANCING THE DEVELOPMENT OF INNOVATIVE PRODUCTS AND SERVICES AND PROVIDING FOR EFFICIENT SHARING OF BUSINESS RESOURCES. TRANSACTIONS AMONG REPORTABLE SEGMENTS ARE RECORDED AT COST. 3M IS AN INTEGRATED ENTERPRISE CHARACTERIZED BY SUBSTANTIAL INTERSEGMENT COOPERATION, COST ALLOCATIONS AND INVENTORY TRANSFERS. THEREFORE, MANAGEMENT DOES NOT REPRESENT THAT THESE SEGMENTS, IF OPERATED INDEPENDENTLY, WOULD REPORT THE OPERATING INCOME INFORMATION SHOWN. THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN OPERATING INCOME AND PRE-TAX INCOME RELATES TO INTEREST INCOME AND INTEREST EXPENSE, WHICH ARE NOT ALLOCATED TO BUSINESS SEGMENTS.

115

TABLE OF CONTENTS

EFFECTIVE IN THE

THIRD

QUARTER OF 201

5

, WITHIN THE

HEALTH CARE

BUSINESS SEGMENT,

THE COMPANY FORMED THE ORAL CARE SOLUTIONS DIVISION, WHICH COMBINED THE FORMER 3M ESPE AND 3M UNITEK DIVISIONS.

